# Success Metrics

A successful production platform meets these metrics:

- uptime greater than 99.9 percent
- deployment success rate above 95 percent
- incident response time under 10 minutes
- recovery time under 30 minutes
- infrastructure cost efficiency maintained

---

# Advanced Capabilities

## Chaos Engineering

Introduce controlled failures to test resilience.

Examples:

- simulated service crashes
- network disruptions
- dependency outages

---

## Auto Scaling

Infrastructure must automatically scale based on:

- CPU usage
- request rate
- queue depth

---

## Cost Optimization

Continuously optimize cloud spending using:

- autoscaling
- instance rightsizing
- storage lifecycle policies
- reserved capacity

---

## Disaster Recovery

Implement recovery mechanisms:

- automated database backups
- cross-region replication
- documented recovery playbooks

